Enum IndexUtil.IndexType

  • Object
    • Enum<IndexUtil.IndexType>
      • senselogic.sitevision.api.search.index.IndexUtil.IndexType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<IndexUtil.IndexType>
    Enclosing interface:
    IndexUtil

    @Requireable(value="IndexUtil.IndexType")
public static enum IndexUtil.IndexType
extends Enum<IndexUtil.IndexType>
    Type of default index, used by IndexUtil.

    Example of how to get the USER_IDENTITY type:

    • Using Velocity:
      
       #set ($instanceCreatorUtil = $sitevisionUtils.instanceCreatorUtil)
       #set ($enumClassName = 'senselogic.sitevision.api.search.index.IndexUtil$IndexType') ## Note the '$' separator...
       #set ($userIdentityEnum = $instanceCreatorUtil.getEnumInstance($enumClassName, 'USER_IDENTITY'))
    • Using server-side JavaScript:
      
       var userIdentityEnum = require('IndexUtil.IndexType.USER_IDENTITY');
    Since:
    Sitevision 3.6
